      • shiftLeft

        public boolean shiftLeft(SortedBlock<BTreeKey<K>> left,
                         SortedBlock<BTreeKey<K>> right,
                         BTreeKey<K> parent)
        Given two blocks this methods moves keys from the right block to the left (starting with moving the parent into the left block, moving the smallest key in the right block to the parent and so on. The method only shifts if it gains anything from it, i.e continously check the current shift. if(parent.byteSize()+left.getDataBytes() >= right.getDataBytes() - right.getFirstKey().byteSize()){ break; } Shifting is needed when balancing blocks in the BTree index.
        Parameters:
        left - block with smaller values.
        right - block with larger values.
        parent - the parent node in the index.
        Returns:
        true if at least one key was shifted

      • shiftRight

        public boolean shiftRight(SortedBlock<BTreeKey<K>> left,

                          BTreeKey<K> parent)
        The same as for shiftLeft but in the other direction
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if at least one key was shifted

      • generateSeparator

        public BTreeKey<K> generateSeparator(SortedBlock<KeyValue<K,V>> small,
                                     SortedBlock<KeyValue<K,V>> large)
        Generate a new separator between two blocks, i.e the smallest key that would separate a a block with smaller keys and a block with larger keys. If the BPlusTree does not contain a separator the smallest key in the larger block will be returned.
        Parameters:
        small - a block with smaller keys
        large - a block with larger keys
        Returns:
        a separator
